# Processes & System Monitoring Lab

## Commands Learned
- ps
- ps aux
- ps aux | grep <process>
- top
- kill <PID>
- kill -9 <PID>
- uptime
- free -h
- df -h

## Key Learnings
- PID identifies each process
- top shows real-time system activity
- kill stops processes
- System monitoring is critical for performance and troubleshooting
# Linux Networking Lab

## Commands Learned
- ip a / ifconfig
- ping
- route -n / ip route
- netstat / ss
- curl
- traceroute
- nslookup

## Key Learnings
- ip/ifconfig shows IP and interfaces
- ping tests connectivity
- traceroute shows network path
- netstat/ss shows listening services
- curl checks server responses
- nslookup helps with DNS troubleshooting
